`4++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++``
`8Keywords``   : Look
`8Categories`` : 
`4++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++``

`8Syntax:``  

 * look
 * look    <object>
 * look    <character>
 * look    <direction>
 * look    <keyword>
 * look in <container>
 * look in <corpse>
 * look in <portal>

 Look is a command that, as it suggests, looks at or in something or someone.
It can be used to look at objects, or people/creatures, and to look in
directions, to see the room and contents that lie in that direction. It can
also be used to look in something, be that a container, a corpse, or a portal
to see the destination.

`4++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++``
